total kinetic energy \begin{equation} KE_{rigid} = \frac{1}{2} M{V_{cm}}^2 + \frac{1}{2} I_{CM}{\omega_{CM}}^2 \end{equation}
torque from gravity For even non rigid bodies, the following follows:
\begin{equation} \vec{\tau}_g = \vec{R}_{CM} \times M\vec{g} \end{equation}
Actually, this follows for any \(f\) (like \(g\)) evenly applied across point masses.
